<!---
Add the doctype declaration x

Add the html element x

Add the head element x

It should have a title element with the contents, Order a Melongram!  x

Add the body element x

The contents of your page should go in the body x

=======

Now, add HTML to mark-up the introductory content. x

Order a Melongram should go in an h1 element x

The next two paragraphs should both go in p elements x
==========
The next section (titled, “Melon Options”) should display a table of melons and their prices.

Melon Options should go in an h2 element x

The next paragraph introduces the table of melons, so put it in a p element x

Create a table element to contain each row of melons and their prices x

Each row should go in a tr element x

Each row should contain two td elements: one for the name of the melon, and one for its price x
========
Place the header, Order Form in an h2 element x

Create a form to contain the rest of the content x

Inside the form:

Add a text input to take in the user’s name. It should have the name, name x

Add a text input to take in the Melongram recipient’s name. It should have the name, recipient x

Under Choose a melon, create a select element with the name, melon x

Put each melon in an option element. 
Each option should have a value that’s the lowercase version of the melon name. 
For example, the value for Watermelon should be watermelon

Under When should we deliver?, create a set of radio buttons for each option 

Each radio button should have the name, time

The value for Morning is am

The value for Evening is pm

The value for Any time is any
-->

#open in browser to check it out!

<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
    <title>
        <h1>Order a Melongram!</h1>
    </title>
</head>
<body>
   <!--- <h1>Order a Melongram!</h1> -->
<p>There's no better way to show a loved one you care than with a Melongram.</p>

<p>
Each Melongram comes with a custom message printed on high-quality cardstock
and your choice of a hand-picked, premium melon.
</p>

<h2>Melon Options</h2>

<p>
Choose from one of these melons:
<!---table tag! tr goes around each pair of td-->
<table>
    <tr><td>Watermelon</td><td> $1,200.00</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Canteloupe</td><td> $400.00</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Honeydew</td><td> $1,750.00</td></tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2>Order Form</h2>
<!---getting user name-->

<form>

<label for="Name">
    Name
</label>
    <input type="text" name="User" id="Name">

</p><!---shipping info-->
    <p>Recipient
<input type="text" name="Recipient">
</p>
<!---melon selection-->
<select name="Choose a melon">
    <option value="Watermelon"> Watermelon </option>
    <option value="Canteloupe"> Canteloupe </option>
    <option value="Honeydew"> Honeydew </option>
</select>

<p>When should we deliver?</p>
    <input type="radio" name="time" value="am"> Morning
    <input type="radio" name="time" value="pm"> Evening
    <input type="radio" name="time" value="any"> Any time


<p> Enter your message:
<!---text area with name message-->
    <textarea name="message"> </textarea>
</p>
<p>Subscribe to our newsletter
<!---create a checkbox with name 'subscribe' and value 'yes'-->
<input type = "checkbox" name="subscribe" value = "yes"> Yes
</p>
<!---add a submit button-->
<p><input type = "submit"></p>

</form>
</body>